field.name: content
field.value:
Display matrix actions and roles

The Administrator is able to manage the actions that could be performed by each role in the system.

  • The user selects in the Administration menu the option Manage roles and actions (1-2).

 

 

 

 

 

 

  • The screen with section "Manage actions per role" opens (1).
  • In the screen are listed in a matrix view all unique actions that could be performed (lines) (3) and all existing business roles in the system (columns) (4-5-6-7).
    • The actions in the matrix are displayed with their labels.
    • The Administrator role is not listed.
    • There is a scroll (8) in the screen.
    • The user could filter the actions in the list (9-10).
    • There is "Edit actions per role" option (11).
 

Note: If a new action is configured in the system, then it dynamically is displayed in the list.

 

 

 

 

The user filters the actions by "Create" (1-2).

  • All actions that include the entered criteria are displayed (3).
  • There is "Edit actions per role" option (4).

 

 

Select/ Deselect action per role

The Administrator is able to configure the actions that each role could perform.

In the Manage actions per role screen, there is action "Edit actions per role" - (see the screen above).

  • When the user selects "Edit actions per role", then for each role the administrator has option to select / deselect (1-2) the actions that could be performed by that role.
    • Only the actions set per role could be performed by that role in the system (the selected check boxes - 1).
  • When the user is ready with setting the actions per role then he must Save (3) the settings he made.
    • There is a Cancel option (4) which cancels the changes.

Add filter per action performed by a role

The administrator is able to add additional filters based on the relationship between an user and an object, based on which an action could be performed by a role or not.

Example: An user with role Contributor to be able to Add Thumbnail to object only if he is the Creator of that object.

  • For each action per role there is ability to select from all described relationships in the model between user and other objects.
    • The user clicks in the "Select filters" field (1) for the Role Contributor and action Add Thumbnail and selects the relation (2-3-4).
      • Each relation may be removed (5) from the filter.
  • One or more relationships could be selected per action/role (1-2-3). The logical operator between the relationships is OR.
  • The selected action could be executed by the user with that role, only of the user who is in the selected relationship with the object on which the action exists.
